//Glenohumeral osteoarthritis

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 - Bones of Shoulder MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled
When I select 'Glenohumeral osteoarthritis' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Severity of glenohumeral osteoarthritis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Sclerosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Subchondral edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Subchondral cysts' checkbox is enabled
And 'Chondropathy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteophytes' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cuff arthropathy' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Severity of glenohumeral osteoarthritis' checkbox
Then 'Moderate' radio button is enabled
And 'Severe' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Chondropathy' checkbox
Then 'Chondrocalcinosis' checkbox is enabled

And 'Grade I' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade II' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade III' radio button is enabled
And 'Grade IV' radio button is enabled

And 'Largest diameter' input field is enabled

And 'Humeral head' radio button is enabled
And 'Glenoid' radio button is enabled
And 'Bipolar' radio button is enabled
